    },
    {
      "id": "95c842414282ff7818894274de3d2c1b5cc920b8",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 308,
        "name": "Amir Shehata",
        "email": "ashehata@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "ashehata"
      },
      "date": "2020-05-04 15:25:12.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nI'm not sure I agree with the direction of this functional change. I believe per network type timeout + considering ULP timeout in determining the LNet/LND timeout makes more sense. The initial purpose of this is to reduce the complexity for the user from having to independently tune 3 different timeouts, ptlrpc adaptive timeout, LNet timeout and LND timeout.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "bb5390a819b9a5db173319b071d06708bab266bb",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 148,
        "name": "Chris Horn",
        "email": "chris.horn@hpe.com",
        "username": "hornc"
      },
      "date": "2020-05-04 15:28:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nWell, the user doesn't need to. The default behavior is unchanged. This just provides a mechanism to tweak things if you want or need to.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "059afbb47a5623b50513f94249a1e4a7f8870535",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 148,
        "name": "Chris Horn",
        "email": "chris.horn@hpe.com",
        "username": "hornc"
      },
      "date": "2020-05-04 18:02:12.000000000",
      "message": "Abandoned\n\nAfter discussing this issue with Amir I've realized that the ability to set per-LND timeouts that take precedence over the global timeout obviates the need to have the global timeout be tunable. As such, I'll abandon this patch and rework the series to:\n1. Fix the lnet level timeout calculation \n2. Make the lnet level timeout readable from lnetctl/sysfs \n3. Allow LNDs to override the default",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    }
  ],
